{
  "stem": "10768.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "The patients that came there were mostly either with fever or nerve of sciatica because of the rain and sleeping on, on on mud or on the ground.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "From there, I don't remember exactly the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But this was probably already June 1944 when we said we're going forwards.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And our hospital, again, put the few, the few tents and equipment that we had, and our personal belongings, which was only a military coat and, and a knapsack in which we had, you know, one change of linen.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we came, which was in a corner, between the Vistula River and another liver-- river.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "The other river I think was Pilica.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And there we were told to start cleaning in a town, which was called Garwolin.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We were told to clean-- to clean-- you know what-- stables which were used for horses.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Apparently, a very rich Polack had there the stables.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And either he ran away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "He took out some of the horses, or the Russian took away the horses.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "We were cleaning there that our sick people should be able to come there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Our hospital could not come into any of the buildings, because the buildings-- we were sometimes, when we were full, will could take in as many as 2,000 people.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But there was no building enough to accommodate so many people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And most of the work was done in tents.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "The kitchen was in one tent and the operating room was another tent.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "There was perhaps one little room where a doctor was to examine the patient-- something like that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "When we came to Garwolin, after we cleaned these stables, two weeks later they say, no, the Germans went already further.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We can go somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "From Garwolin, we came to Otwock.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
